Name: SMF30RRG
Description: Restart group for element in SMF30RNM.

Name: SMF30RSN
Description: The system name for the system on which the element was initially started. blank, for the initial start.

Name: SMF30RGT
Description: The time (local) when the element issued the IXCARM macro with the REGISTER parameter, in hundredths of a second.

Name: SMF30RGD
Description: The date when the element issued the REGISTER request, in the form 0cyydddF. See Standard SMF record header for a detailed description.

Name: SMF30RWT
Description: The time (local) when the element issued the IXCARM macro with the WAITPRED parameter, in hundredths of a second. This field will be zero if this function was not requested.

Name: SMF30RWD
Description: The date when the element issued IXCARM with the WAITPRED parameter, in the form 0cyydddF (where ‘F’ is the sign). This field will be zero if this function was not requested.

Name: SMF30RYT
Description: The time (local) when the element issued the IXCARM macro with the READY parameter, in hundredths of a second.

Name: SMF30RYD
Description: The date when this element issued the IXCARM macro with the READY parameter, in the format 0cyydddF (where ‘F’ is the sign).

Name: SMF30RTT
Description: The time (local) when the element was deregistered, in hundredths of a second. This field will be zero if this element is not yet deregistered or if it ended abnormally.

Name: SMF30RTD
Description: The date when this element was deregistered, in the format 0cyydddF. See Standard SMF record header for a detailed description. This field will be zero if this element is not yet deregistered or if it ended abnormally.
